\lettrine[lines=4]{\color{black!45}M}{atter} is everywhere around you, from the water you drink to the air you inhale. Matter is made of elements and elements are made of atoms. Even the atoms of an elements can be different, having distinct number of protons and neutrons. This chapter covers the principles of the atomic structure. You will learn what makes an atom and will be able to quantify the particles that make atoms. Perhaps more importantly, you will also learn about the periodic table of the elements and the different types of chemical formulas. 
